  "slug": "epic-hot-chocolate",
  "title": "Epic Hot Chocolate (Not Dairy-Free)",
  "subtitle": "Rich, thick drinking chocolate made from scratch with real dark chocolate",
  "excerpt": "A stovetop hot chocolate thickened with cornflour and real dark chocolate, spiced with cinnamon and a pinch of salt. Makes four generous mugs. The mix keeps in a jar so you can make a cup whenever you want.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook, a recipe she's made many times in her own kitchen.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A proper hot chocolate made with real dark chocolate and a dry mix you blend ahead. The cornflour thickens the milk as it heats so you get a rich, almost claggy texture rather than a thin cocoa drink. Makes four mugs from one batch of milk."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make a bigger jar of the dry mix and keep it in the cupboard. You need around ten heaped tablespoons per litre of milk."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
